clusters.title: Supreme Court Strikes Down Trump's Tariffs, Markets React
clusters.summary: The U.S. Supreme Court ruled 6-3 to strike down most of President Trump's tariffs, leading to a decline in U.S. futures and mixed reactions in global markets. clusters.title: Killing of Drug Lord El Mencho Triggers Violence in Mexico
clusters.summary: Nemesio Oseguera Cervantes, known as 'El Mencho' and leader of the Jalisco New Generation Cartel, was killed in a military operation in Mexico. His death has led to a surge of violence across the country, prompting school closures and flight suspensions in affected areas. The incident highlights ongoing challenges in Mexico's battle against organized crime and the potential for increased instability.

items.title: Killing of Mexican drug cartel boss ‘El Mencho’ triggers wave of violence
items.description:
Schools close and flights suspended after military raid kills Jalisco New Generation Cartel leader Nemesio Rubén Oseguera Cervantes

• Who was El Mencho, the former police officer who co-founded an ultraviolent cartel in Mexico?

Whole areas of western Mexico have been all but shut down after a surge in cartel violence sparked by a military raid that killed one of the world’s most wanted drug traffickers, known as “El Mencho”.

Schools were closed in several Mexican states, and foreign governments warned their citizens to stay inside after the drug lord, whose real name is Nemesio Rubén Oseguera Cervantes, was declared dead on Sunday.
